#     untouched files are grandfathered in practice (Boy Scout rule applies
#     on next touch). Full scan is available via `npm run firestore:indexes:audit`
#     for CI jobs and manual audits.
#   - Rationale: a per-file gate matches "zero tolerance on touch" while
#     allowing incremental cleanup of the backlog without blocking unrelated
#     commits. Accidental deletion of an index still in use by untouched
#     files is expected to be caught by CI, not pre-commit.
# =============================================================================

INDEX_COVERAGE_SCRIPT="scripts/check-firestore-index-coverage.js"
